HEADWORD: Uncinata
<hw>Un`ci*na"ta</hw> <pr>(⟦ucr⟧n"s⟦icr⟧*n⟦amac⟧"t⟦adot⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. L. <ets>uncinus</ets> a hook.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A division of marine chaetopod annelids which
are furnished with uncini, as the serpulas and sabellas.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

